<section id="impress_remote_guide">
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id180820171850105346">
  <bookmark_value>Impress slide show;remote control</bookmark_value>
  <bookmark_value>remote control;Bluetooth connection</bookmark_value>
  <bookmark_value>remote control;controlling slide show</bookmark_value>
  <bookmark_value>Impress Remote;controlling slide show</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>


<paragraph id="hd_id170820171152085523" role="heading" level="1" xml-lang="en-US"><link href="text/simpress/guide/impress_remote.xhp">Slide Show Remote Control - Impress Remote User Guide</link></paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171152388332" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US"><ahelp hid=".">%PRODUCTNAME Impress Remote is an open source application available for Android and iOS operating systems, which let the users to controls their %PRODUCTNAME Impress slide show with a mobile device.</ahelp></paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id18082017203814366" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US"><image id="img_id180820172037407615" src="media/helpimg/impress_remote_icon.png" width="2cm" height="2cm"><alt xml-lang="en-US" id="alt_id180820172037407615">Impress Remote Icon</alt></image></paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171219426143" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Impress Remote displays slides thumbnails in the mobile device screen with its notes below. Slide your finger in the mobile screen to go forward or backward in the presentation. You can also display a mosaic of slides to jump directly to the desired one for easier presentation dynamic.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171556596990" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Connection between the computer holding the %PRODUCTNAME Impress presentation and the mobile device is done through Bluetooth or network link.</paragraph>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213379781" role="heading" level="2" xml-lang="en-US">Impress Remote Features</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171213377063" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Impress Remote is a very useful application to let you for control slide shows at a distance of the computer, enabling you to walk while doing your presentation. Its main features are:</paragraph>

<list type="unordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213372148" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Control the slide show</emph> with finger gestures and taps on the mobile device screen.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id18082017152608187" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Slide objects animations</emph> are triggered with taps on the mobile screen.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171807276358" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Slide Previews</emph>: The presentation slides can be previewed in the mobile device when both the computer and device are connected.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213376498" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Speaker notes</emph>: there is an exclusive speaker notes section below the slides on your phone where all the slide notes will be displayed.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213378089" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Stop-watch</emph>: The stop watch is a feature in Impress Remote where the timer can be set for each slides while you are doing your presentation.</paragraph>
  </listitem></list>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213373502" role="heading" level="2" xml-lang="en-US">Requirements:</paragraph>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213372327" role="heading" level="3" xml-lang="en-US">Computer:</paragraph>

<list type="unordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213375117" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">GNU/Linux, Windows or OSX. </paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213371179" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Bluetooth or network connectivity.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213374973" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">%PRODUCTNAME version 4.1 or higher.</paragraph>
  </listitem></list>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213374790" role="heading" level="3" xml-lang="en-US">Mobile device:</paragraph>

<list type="unordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213372067" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">A phone or tablet with·Android 2.3 or higher or iOS with Bluetooth or network connectivity.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213375360" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Impress Remote application installed in the mobile device.</paragraph>
  </listitem></list>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171556594902" role="heading" level="2" xml-lang="en-US">Downloading and Installing Impress Remote in your mobile device</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171556595054" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Download Impress Remote from the Android Play Store or Apple Store by typing for "Impress Remote" in the search area of the application store of the mobile device. Be sure that the results bring Impress Remote from The Document Foundation (TDF). Install Impress Remote in the mobile device as with other mobile applications.</paragraph>

<paragraph id="hd_id180820171526083520" role="heading" level="2" xml-lang="en-US">Impress Remote Settings</paragraph>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id180820171851119861">
  <bookmark_value>Impress Remote;settings</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>

<paragraph id="par_id180820171526081809" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">With Impress Remote active in the mobile device and in the Computer page, access the Setting page taping the right corner of the screen. The following settings are available:</paragraph>

<list type="unordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id180820171526087374" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Volume keys actions</emph> : mark to enable the mobile device volume keys to go forward when pressing the volume up button and move backward when pressing the volume down button.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id180820171526085600" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Keep screen on</emph>: mark to prevent the automatic screen off and device auto locking when using Impress Remote.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id180820171526082838" role="ul_item" xml-lang="en-US"><emph>Quiet mode</emph>: put the device in silent mode to avoid audio notification of incoming calls or other messages. This setting does not affect vibration mode previously set.</paragraph>
  </listitem></list>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213387590" role="heading" level="2" xml-lang="en-US">Connecting the computer to the mobile device</paragraph>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id18082017185147849">
  <bookmark_value>Impress Remote;connecting to computer</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>

<paragraph id="par_id17082017174417603" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Activate Bluetooth on both device and computer and pair them. Refer to the instructions manuals of the mobile device and computer operating system for enabling, setting up a Bluetooth identifier and pairing. Once the pairing is established, the mobile device is ready to control the presentation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171744189201" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Alternatively you can connect through a network (including wi-fi). In this case, both computer and device must be connected to in the same network.</paragraph>

<paragraph id="hd_id170820171213403538" role="heading" level="3" xml-lang="en-US">Enabling Impress Remote control in %PRODUCTNAME Impress</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id17082017174418977" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">To run an Impress slide show, you must allow Impress to be controlled by the mobile device. Proceed as follows:</paragraph>

<list type="ordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213404007" role="ol_item" xml-lang="en-US">·Open %PRODUCTNAME Impress.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213414955" role="ol_item" xml-lang="en-US">·Go to <item type="menuitem">Tools – Options – %PRODUCTNAME Impress – General</item>.·It should give you the screen in the figure below.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213449763" role="ol_item" xml-lang="en-US">·In the presentation Options, Click on the <emph>Enable remote control</emph> option and click <emph>OK</emph>. </paragraph>
  </listitem>
</list>
<paragraph id="par_id170820171213444783" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Close %PRODUCTNAME Impress and start again.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="par_id15531" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US"><image id="img_id23615" src="media/screenshots/cui/ui/optionsdialog/impressoptionsgeneraldialog.png" width="20.001cm" height="13cm"><alt xml-lang="en-US" id="alt_id23615">{ENTER ALTERNATE DESCRIPTION HERE}</alt></image></paragraph>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="hid/modules/simpress/ui/optimpressgeneralpage/presentationframe" id="bm_id24863" localize="false"/>

<paragraph id="par_id170820171213446581" role="heading" level="3" xml-lang="en-US">Controlling the slide show:</paragraph>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id180820171852161224">
  <bookmark_value>Impress Remote;using</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>

<paragraph id="par_id180820171526085922" role="tip" xml-lang="en-US">Disable screen saving and screen locking from the mobile device as shown above previous of running a slide show. Ensure the mobile device has enough battery power for the show duration.</paragraph>

<list type="ordered">
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213445336" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">·Make sure both device and computer are already paired via Bluetooth or network connection.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213442936" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">·Open the presentation you want to show in %PRODUCTNAME Impress.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213449161" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">·Open Impress Remote application on the mobile device and select the Bluetooth ID of the computer,</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213445296" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">·Once you clicked on the computers name it will automatically load the presentation slides on the Impress Remote with the notes section.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213444433" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">·Slide your finger left or right on the mobile screen to change the slides. Slide notes are in the bottom part of the mobile screen.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213449235" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">Optionally set the timer for each slide display from the application on mobile device. </paragraph>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
    <paragraph id="par_id170820171213441462" role="paragraph" xml-lang="en-US">The slides can also be changed with the volume keys on the mobile device. To enable it, open settings and enable volume key actions in the Impress Remote.</paragraph>
  </listitem>
</list>

